    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nfrom: https://old.reddit.com/r/neovim/comments/1jdcqp7/nvimctxingest_easily_share_project_ctx_with_ur_llm/mid7v1i/\n\nAI plugins often want to generate a useful digest of the workspace. A common task related to that, is to ignore paths that match `.gitignore` configuration.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n- `vim.glob` supports gitignore glob expressions. `vim.glob.from_git()` ?\n- `vim.fs` can easily produce a project file tree which excludes `.gitignore` (and respects subdirectory-local `.gitignore` files). Or document how to do this, if it's already well-supported.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
